                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12868385" author="bluk" created="Mon, 17 May 2010 20:19:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made a change so that the getSize() will return -1 (therefore not returning any value for the Content-Length).  This is probably the safest fix for performance reasons and should work across all HTTP 1.1 environments.  If you would rather have the Content-Length be re-calculated, please re-open the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12868398" author="hudson" created="Mon, 17 May 2010 20:38:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5 #333 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/333/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/333/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Return -1 for the StringProvider size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will now not fill in the Content-Length&lt;br/&gt;
in the response headers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to Shay Tsadok for reporting the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WINK-282&quot; title=&quot;StringProvider may not work properly when trying to write an &amp;quot;Xml string&amp;quot; &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WINK-282&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WINK-282&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12869511" author="shayts7" created="Thu, 20 May 2010 07:51:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Bryant,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix! Since we are using Http 1.1 this solution fits.&lt;br/&gt;
BTW - I would like to take the latest Wink version including your fix, In order to avoid custom &quot;StringProvider&quot; in my code.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve noticed that the latest build is from 4-May-2010 (taken from: &lt;a href=&quot;http://apache.mivzakim.net/incubator/wink/1.1-incubating/apache-wink-1.1-incubating.zip&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://apache.mivzakim.net/incubator/wink/1.1-incubating/apache-wink-1.1-incubating.zip&lt;/a&gt;), Is there a chance to promote the build?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Shay &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
